                            <container4
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <title2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545824678,1651545825694]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-03-20T10:54:00.619-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="Turning science into breakthrough medicines "
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h2"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-03-27T14:08:17.290-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>From blood cancers to Hepatitis C virus, our Discovery Files series reveals how we create new possibilities for patients turning breakthrough science into new medicines.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>These scientific scenarios may seem distinctly different, but they have one thing in common: After years of perseverance, scientists reached a “eureka” moment in the lab that helped make a molecule a reality to form the basis of a transformative medicine. Now, a new documentary series – The Discovery Files — reveals the behind-the-scenes stories that resulted in these pivotal moments.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Discovery science can be a long, arduous process, plagued by a high failure rate. But the Discovery Files episodes demonstrate the tenacity, rigor and out-of-the-box thinking of AbbVie scientists as they chase bold goals to help patients get the solution they need, every single day.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Part of what drives AbbVie scientists is the core purpose and aspiration of our company’s robust discovery research group: to turn science into cures.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“We are not interested in therapies that are iterative in their benefit for patients. Rather we aim to invent breakthrough medicines,” says Jonathon Sedgwick, VP &amp;amp; global head of discovery research, AbbVie. “That comes with many years of experimenting, failing, learning, but always persisting, to find therapies that are truly impactful.”&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Though we strive for “cures”, these remain elusive. However, AbbVie scientists always aim to elevate the standard of care, aspiring to have the majority of AbbVie’s medicines considered first-in-kind, meaning they target a novel disease pathway or use a new or unique therapeutic modality that provides benefit for patients. &lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4>
                            <video_714167463
                                cq:styleIds="[1]"
                                jcr:created="{Date}2023-06-12T02:16:50.415-04:00"
                                jcr:createdBy="SCHAFSM"
                                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-06-15T09:48:05.287-04:00"
                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/video/v2/video"
                                brightcoveAutoPlay="false"
                                btnText="Watch 2:33"
                                descriptiveIframeTitle="Discovery Files: The Eureka Moment Behind a Scientific Discovery"
                                fileReference="/content/dam/abbvie-com2/images/stories/what-does-it-take-to-discover-a-new-medicine/discoveryfiles-mitchel-yt.jpg"
                                loopVideo="false"
                                showBrightcoveControls="false"
                                showPlayerControls="false"
                                showRelatedContent="false"
                                showVideoInfo="false"
                                textIsRich="true"
                                title="Discovery Files: The Eureka Moment Behind a Scientific Discovery"
                                videoType="youtube"
                                youtubeAutoPlay="true"
                                youtubeUrl="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/45GzoyuWP2I?rel=0"/>
                            <container4_copy
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <separator_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756423318]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-06-12T02:18:52.472-04:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="SCHAFSM"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-06-12T02:18:52.472-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="SCHAFSM"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545824678,1651545825694]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-03-20T10:54:12.851-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="Motivated by patient impact"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h2"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-03-27T14:45:25.596-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>Scientists aren’t satisfied by the status quo, especially when they know a better option may be possible, according to longtime cancer researcher Andy Souers, Ph.D., a distinguished research fellow within AbbVie’s oncology discovery research team. Souers and his team are behind a blood cancer discovery featured in the second episode of “Discovery Files”, which targets a family of proteins many in the pharmaceutical industry previously considered “undruggable.” The drive to find another option beyond chemotherapy for people with certain kinds of leukemias motivated the team to keep experimenting for years before ultimately finding their “eureka” moment.  &lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“One huge advantage we had was this culture at AbbVie, which basically allowed us to do any sort of exploration we needed to reach the objective,” Souers explains in the episode. &lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4_copy>
                            <quote
                                cq:styleIds="[1000000000000]"
                                jcr:created="{Date}2023-06-12T02:19:39.627-04:00"
                                jcr:createdBy="SCHAFSM"
                                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-03-27T14:03:22.787-04:00"
                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/quote"
                                attributionName="Seble Wagaw"
                                attributionTitle=" VP, development sciences, AbbVie"
                                quote="The journey showed us that we have the capability and the drive to keep working every day to discover and develop new treatments for people who need them. "
                                quoteType="regular"
                                textSize="h0"/>
                            <container4_copy_copy
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <separator_copy_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756423318]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-06-12T02:18:52.472-04:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="SCHAFSM"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-06-12T02:18:52.472-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="SCHAFSM"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545824678,1651545825694]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-03-20T10:54:22.570-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="The same patient drive, across disease areas"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h2"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-06-14T17:12:21.461-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="SCHAFSM"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>Visit any AbbVie lab or research hub and you’ll hear similar stories, whether it’s from immunology scientists chasing a better way to treat different autoimmune diseases or practicing physicians searching for new medicines that could help relieve devastating movement disorders.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>“Discovery Files” examines how these teams stay motivated and use creativity and persistence to create patient impact.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>In episode three, for example, we meet an AbbVie virology team on a quest to end Hepatitis C virus (HCV) infection, a prevalent disease &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.who.int/en/news-room/fact-sheets/detail/hepatitis-c&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>affecting about 58 million people worldwide&lt;/a>.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4_copy_copy>
                            <video
                                cq:styleIds="[1]"
                                jcr:created="{Date}2023-06-12T02:23:56.602-04:00"
                                jcr:createdBy="SCHAFSM"
                                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-06-15T09:48:48.532-04:00"
                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/video/v2/video"
                                brightcoveAutoPlay="false"
                                btnText="Watch 4:24"
                                descriptiveIframeTitle="Discovery Files: Hepatitis C Virus"
                                fileReference="/content/dam/abbvie-com2/images/stories/what-does-it-take-to-discover-a-new-medicine/discoveryfiles-hepatitis-c-virus-yt.png"
                                loopVideo="false"
                                showBrightcoveControls="false"
                                showPlayerControls="false"
                                showRelatedContent="false"
                                showVideoInfo="false"
                                textIsRich="true"
                                title="Discovery Files: Hepatitis C Virus"
                                videoType="youtube"
                                youtubeAutoPlay="true"
                                youtubeUrl="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/rMy4Bo6Go7U?rel=0"/>
                            <container4_copy_copy_712417177
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <separator_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756423318]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-06-12T02:18:52.472-04:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="SCHAFSM"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-06-12T02:18:52.472-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="SCHAFSM"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <text2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-06-14T17:15:51.663-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="SCHAFSM"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>Building off their own research around HIV, the team aimed to find a way to stop the virus from replicating, lowering the viral load in the body and blocking proteins necessary for the virus’ survival. But the journey didn’t end there – it took years and many iterations until the real “aha” moment; the team had to work counter-intuitively, building molecules larger instead of smaller and targeting all major HCV genotypes instead of just some.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>The stories of the Discovery Files series demonstrate that “good enough” is never good enough, for those at AbbVie searching for tomorrow’s scientific breakthroughs. One of the series’ featured scientists, Seble Wagaw, VP, development sciences, AbbVie, explains it best. “The journey show(s) us that we have the capability and the drive to keep working every day to discover and develop new treatments for people who need them.”&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <separator_1438601535
